ut I know I need the correct artifact dependencies. I have the POM file, but I might also need additional dependencies like cglib or asm. It looks like jarjar is bundled too, but I won't be using Docker.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"sisu-guice 2.9.1 does not need external services or extra Maven dependencies for normal Guice coverage, but AOP/CGLIB coverage on modern JDKs requires opening java.lang because the bundled CGLIB reflects on ClassLoader#defineClass.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"When generated tests exercise method interception, BytecodeGen, Enhancer, MethodProxy, or other bundled CGLIB paths, configure both JVM test execution and native-image build/run with `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED`. Prefer public Guice APIs for coverage; if tests directly target bundled internals in 2.9.1, use the relocated `$`-prefixed class names present in the artifact, such as `com.google.inject.internal.util.$MapMaker` and `com.google.inject.internal.cglib.proxy.$MethodProxy`, not the unprefixed 2.1.7 internal names.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Existing 2.1.7 tests import unprefixed internal classes that are no longer present in the 2.9.1 default jar, which explains the javac failures.\",\n    \"The artifact bundles relocated ASM/CGLIB classes; adding external ASM or CGLIB dependencies would likely be misleading rather than necessary.\",\n    \"SLF4J is optional in the POM; only add it if intentionally testing SLF4J logger injection, not for baseline meaningful coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f920c6ee423b32c016a4220ba56608194bc64aed752fd2721\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 507, "output": 1350, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31041, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782718636149, "responseId": "resp_0f920c6ee423b32c016a4220ac9a8c81949c1af5d1e715b54d"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring Logger dependencies**\n\nI’m thinking about whether I need the optional slf4j dependency for testing Logger injection. The usual requirement is the slf4j-api, but does it really contribute to meaningful coverage? Guice can inject either java.util.logging.Logger or org.slf4j.Logger, so I should check that. It looks like if the POM doesn't automatically include slf4j-api, class references could lead to issues. I need to be careful with dependencies unless absolutely necessary, so I should check the documentation for confirmation.\n\n**Reviewing Sisu-Guice usage**\n\nI’m considering Sisu-Guice as related to Guice 3, which is typically used for dependency injection. I think I should check the documentation, possibly on code.google or the Guice wiki, to find more information. There doesn’t seem to be any external service involved, but I know I need the correct artifact dependencies. I have the POM file, but I might also need additional dependencies like cglib or asm. It looks like jarjar is bundled too, but I won't be using Docker.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f920c6ee423b32c016a4220ad604881948e8b5070195efc42\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQiC6XSqFd22dky3aCuCVeWfxbP8C42lmhlHo3ja0xE2POEW24vJMFWVMc678xNws8JhW_vevDNhXZonTRczR_pODo_3T_b9fCAkP7rwoznlF6SFlLrwkmpjYp8jiowGmu8zq1Npx0z_--t6fu36DtzGUIK9jge-liTkGP-7muBPF6W3orE2qsvSEjCcbXRxpkIjXXAh7BX5l6TV3GuHBjTvxcF92Ya3UA0Fwmwq1m-GxvKTG-TkD0EtKY5T4L4buoOFaSLndPDbQKHa5Ydfyzm0hj5voRuC33x8TiU524EmDTCyxT7EbWE-aml-4t3KGymZ073PuOAyYvSi1e5u0wQXPgS7DGboVmE1bI1k3Swa-w72gR67U0GQIRzqbPWiyln9Tz_Ne91HYYSsU5ee0isYL0mtAuKkMb_V1q_106Lo8Z5MhJE0Baf944abevwPP4Bqb5BTQOsMwLdyHhSJctYaSyr-RAqWVW00Yqhh7tHI0cTTf95gt7hr95RYg_bNHiXle6hEk0iAeM-hv4A351lBngD9Vl2lzNnFNdfg0ZbO6cdbhT_8DfmXaQiJ9m2Pwa5jtBn9vouEa3ngS-Y4MnCVqCYEvmG_F9uvRAGqud5wkbxu_fonOEIy-uJUIjRpo46L6Wy7ar9dBpY6T_Fr8JApfhpZuhWwP2tJncM